HEADWORD: Copeman
<hw>Cope"man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D.
<ets>koopman</ets>, fr. <ets>koopen</ets> to buy. See <er>Cope</er>,
<pos>v. i.</pos> <er>Chapman</er>.]</ety> <def>A chapman; a dealer; a
merchant.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He would have sold his part of paradise⟦br⟧
For ready money, had he met a <qex>copeman</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>B.
Jonson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Copenhagen</ent>⟦br⟧
